   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In an inverter system an inverter converts direct current (DC)
to alternating current (AC) that supplies the load.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">A system without a bypass has no alternative supply for the load.
The static switch EA is used to help isolate the system so there is
no feedback to the inverter.</p>
